  <!-- Descriptions -->
  <descriptions>

    <description descriptionType="Abstract">
      Open-source intelligence (OSINT) compilation of visually confirmed equipment
      losses related to the 2022 Russia–Ukraine war, derived from Oryx reporting
      and augmented with image-based entries. The dataset contains categorized
      records of destroyed, damaged, abandoned, and captured military equipment
      for both Russia and Ukraine. The dataset also includes metadata referencing
      images documenting these losses.
    </description>

    <description descriptionType="Methods">
      Data compiled from publicly available imagery and OSINT reports.
      Entries reflect visually confirmed equipment status at the time
      the evidence was documented. Records are cross-checked against
      the Oryx visually confirmed equipment losses database.
    </description>

    <description descriptionType="TechnicalInfo">
      Dataset provided as CSV files containing structured equipment
      loss records and associated image metadata tables.
    </description>

  </descriptions>

